Title: Series: Idee Pittoresche sopra la Fugga in Egitto
Description: Plate 2: dedication with a winged figure of fame bearing the arms of the Prince-Bishop of Wurzburg. 1750/2 Etching
Curator's comments: The series of 'Idee Pittoresche' consists of 27 plates: three introductory, and 24 with the story of the Flight into Egypt. They were etched between 1750-2, and published in 1753 in Wurzburg. The BM has the entire set in an album, and five single prints mounted.
